# Production build config (loaded by `vite build`, i.e. on Vercel).
#
# These are NOT secrets — the host and database name are public and already
# visible in the shipped client bundle. Committing them means a Vercel build
# is correctly pointed at maincloud with no dashboard configuration.
#
# To point production at a different backend, override these in the Vercel
# project's Environment Variables (dashboard values win over this file).
VITE_SPACETIMEDB_HOST=wss://maincloud.spacetimedb.com
VITE_SPACETIMEDB_DB_NAME=spacecards

# Umami (cookieless analytics). The website id is public, like the host/db above
# (it's visible in the shipped bundle). Analytics stays DORMANT while this is
# empty — paste the real id from the Umami dashboard here, or set it in the
# Vercel project's Environment Variables (dashboard wins over this file).
# VITE_UMAMI_SRC is optional and defaults to https://cloud.umami.is/script.js;
# set it only to point at a self-hosted Umami.
VITE_UMAMI_WEBSITE_ID=50e9affa-1928-4c74-9255-504d3311a1ca

# Note: the Google OAuth client id is NOT here — it's public, shared config that
# the client imports directly from the server's single source of truth
# (spacetimedb/src/constants.ts). The host/db above stay in env because they
# genuinely differ between local dev and production; the client id does not.
